<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="How Byzantique handles (and mostly doesn't want) your data.">
  <nav class="crumbs ui"><a href="/">Byzantique</a><span class="sep">›</span>Privacy Policy</nav>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Last updated: June 9, 2026</p>

  <p>
    When you visit this website, it is also visiting you — though, here, rather less than
    most places on the Internet. Byzantique is a small static site. I don't run my own
    servers or ad networks; the site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages and uses
    <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong>, which is privacy-friendly and
    <strong>cookieless</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage Data</h2>
  <p>
    Like nearly every website, some Usage Data may be collected automatically. This can
    include your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address, browser type and version, the
    pages of this website that you visit, the time and date of your visit, and basic
    performance measurements such as how quickly pages load for you. With
    Cloudflare Web Analytics this information is <strong>aggregated</strong> — used to count
    visits, see which pages are read, and monitor how fast the site is for real visitors — and
    is <strong>not</strong> tied to a profile of you or used to identify you personally.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Here's the good news. This site does <strong>not</strong> set advertising or tracking
    cookies, does not use web beacons or pixel tags to follow you, and does not fingerprint
    you or track you across other websites. There is no "little gift known as a cookie — a
    text file filled with inscrutable gibberish" left behind here, and no advertising or
    data-broker partners receiving your information.
  </p>
  <p>
    Your browser always sends some basic information (like your IP address) to any server
    it talks to — that's simply how the Internet works — but this site does not store it in
    a database or sell it to anyone.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    I don't maintain my own database of visitors. Cloudflare keeps aggregate analytics for a
    limited window for the counts above. Frankly, I can't find my keys half the time — I'm
    not about to start building a dossier on you.
  </p>

  <h2>Not for Children</h2>
  <p>
    This website does not address anyone under the age of 13, and does not knowingly collect
    personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 13.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    The security of your data matters, but remember that no method of transmission over the
    Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure. The site is served over HTTPS,
    but absolute security cannot be guaranteed.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
  <p>
    This website may contain links to other websites that are not operated by me. If you
    click a third-party link, you will be directed to that site. I have no control over, and
    assume no responsibility for, the content or privacy practices of any third-party sites —
    review the privacy policy of every site you visit.
  </p>

  <h2>Disclosure of Data</h2>
  <p>
    I do not sell your data. I may be compelled to disclose information for legal reasons.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This privacy policy may change at any time; the date it was last updated is indicated at
    the top of this page.
  </p>

  <h2>In short</h2>
  <p>
    This is a tiny nonprofit website, (barely) maintained in my limited free time — it is not
    a business. I genuinely don't want your data, and I've deliberately chosen hosting and
    analytics that don't want it either.
  </p>

